Stefanl FILECCIA v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7409. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 16, 1936. Donald F. Welday, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Gregory H. Frederick, 'tj. S. Atty., of Detroit, Mich.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel, it is ordered that the appeal in the above-entitled cause be, and the same is, dismissed.
